BFN 

  [Excerpt] A two-day international conference on the 
problems of economic development in the Baltic countries ended 
today. It was organized by the European Union. At the end of 
the event, the leaders of the delegations of Latvia, Lithuania, 
and Estonia, and of the European Union signed an agreement 
creating an information infrastructure in the Baltic lands, 
which will improve communications between governments, banks, 
enterprises, local authorities, and also international 
communications. [passage omitted] 

